目前位置：國立交通大學機構典藏
數位教材
開放式課程






















標題: 台灣史（一）The History of Taiwan I
作者: 黃紹恆蔣淑貞Open Education Office開放教育推動中心
公開日期: 2007
摘要: 課程首頁

	 

	本課程是由交通大學人文社會學系/族群與文化碩士班提供。

	 

	This one-year course is designed for international students with English as the academic language. The first semester covers a period of more than 300 years, from the age of Dutch East Indian Company to 1894 before the Japanese occupation. The second semester will start from Japanese colonial period (1895~1945) onto the contemporary (re)construction of Taiwanese identity. Students are required to do weekly readings, oral presentations, class discussions, and a term paper.課程概述  
This one-year course is designed for international students with English as the academic language. The first semester covers a period of more than 300 years, from the age of Dutch East Indian Company to 1894 before the Japanese occupation. The second semester will start from Japanese colonial period (1895~1945) onto the contemporary (re)construction of Taiwanese identity. Students are required to do weekly readings, oral presentations, class discussions, and a term paper.
 
課程章節  




章節

內容綱要

第一週
導論

第二週
